post_text: We have spent the summer listening, planning, and preparing for the new school year. Now, with the first day of school fast approaching, it is time to put our plans into action. During the Board of Education meeting on Monday, August 10, the Board decided that when the 2020-2021 school year begins on Tuesday, August 25, instruction will be provided using the Hybrid Learning model. For students with the last names beginning A-M, the first day of school will be Thursday, August 27. For students with last names beginning N-Z, the first day of school will be Tuesday, August 25.

post_text:
We have identified some grades and courses that need more instructional time at the start of the year to learn critical skills and concepts. Therefore, we will hold summer school from August 3 – August 14 for students entering 1st grade, 2nd grade, and 8th grade. Students that were enrolled in Principles of Algebra and Geometry (PAG) or Algebra I during the 2019-20 school year will also need to attend. We are committed to the success of each student. While not all students will attend summer school, our #SCCSD teachers will be prepared to differentiate instruction to support every student’s needs at the start of the school year. For more information, visit:
https://www.siouxcityschools.org/news/return-to-learn-update-summer-school-details/

post_text: Today, the Iowa Governor granted all schools the approval to remain closed through the end of this academic year. In this uncertain time, we all must work together to combat the risks of the COVID-19 pandemic. Therefore, all Sioux City Community Schools will remain closed through the end of this school year, but students can continue to participate in voluntary continuous learning from home through June 2.

post_text: Our East High School students are practicing social distancing by sending letters to residents at Bickford Senior Living and Memory Care. We love seeing the thoughtful ways our #SCCSD students are coming together to protect the safety and well-being of this community!
shared_text:
East High Student Council
March 19 at 2:23 AM ·

We haven’t been able to get together, but as has been our motto for many years: Find a way or make one!
Our friends at Bickford Senior Living & Memory Care can’t have visitors or outings in order to protect them during this time. We each chose a person and wrote a letter to him or her. Then to collect them, we left letters in mailboxes, on doorsteps, etc. in order to be safe and follow the guidlines- and they’re on their way! Love always find a way! ❤️Below you’ll find our introductions.

To our Bickford Buddies from your friends at East High Student Council. We can’t wait to hear back from you! ❤️

Principal Taylor helped students celebrate their building-wide achievement by playing "Bingo for Books." Congratulations! #SCCSD

post_text: Have you read a good book lately? Pick one up today, because it’s “National Reading Day!” To celebrate, students at Leeds Elementary School, Sioux City, IA partnered with peer classes to read “If You Give a Dog a Donut” or “Bad Case of the Stripes.” We’re helping kids develop a love for reading! #SCCSD

post_text: As we look ahead to the rest of this week, here are a couple of changes to note. High school and middle school students should plan for an "A-Day" on Thursday, January 23. Thank you.
